com.avaya.csta.binding

Class ConferencedEventPrivateData

  • java.lang.Object
    • ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
      • com.avaya.csta.binding.ConferencedEventPrivateData
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class ConferencedEventPrivateData
extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    Avaya extensions to ConferencedEvent.
    ConferencedEventPrivateData Parameters
    distributingDevice SubjectDeviceID Specifies the original distributing device of the call before the call is conferenced.
    distributingVDN SubjectDeviceID The VDN extension associated with the distributing device. The field gets set under the following conditions.
    • When the application monitors the VDN in question and sees the DeliveredEvent.
    • When the application monitors an agent and receives a call that came from that monitored VDN (that is, in the Delivered, Established, Transferred, and Conferenced events).
    trunkList TrunkInterfaceInfoList Specifies a list of up to 5 trunk groups and trunk members, one for each connected party.
    • connectionAsn
    • trunkGroup
    • trunkMember
    originalCallInfo OriginalCallInfo This parameter is sent with this event for the resulting new call(conferenceCall) of a ConferenceCall request or the retained call of a (manual) conference call operation. For a ConferenceCall, the originalCallInfo includes the original call information originally received by the heldCall specified in the ConferenceCall request. For a manual call conference, the originalCallInfo includes the original call information originally received by the primaryOldCall specified in the event report. The original call information contains the following:
    • reason
    • networkCalledDevice
    • networkCallingDevice
    • trunkGroup
    • trunkMember
    • lookaheadInfo
    • userEnteredCode
    • callLinkageData
    • deviceHistory
